    {
        "content": "<p><code>integrable_indicator</code> requires the assumption of measurablity. I don't see why it needs that. If the integral of <code>f</code> over R is finite, then how could the integral of <code>E.indicator f</code> become infinite? (Assume f is positive everywhere)</p>",
